5) How are exceptions handled in Java? OR Explain exception handling mechanism in Java?

Exceptions in Java are handled using try, catch and finally blocks.

try block : The code or set of statements which are to be monitored for exception are kept in this block.

catch block : This block catches the exceptions occurred in the try block.

finally block : This block is always executed whether exception
is occurred in the try block or not and occurred exception is caught in the catch block or not.